Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #colander{}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all!) (stalks and all!)

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-low heat, add the onion and fry until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @ground cumin{1/2%tsp}, @ras-el-hanout{1%tsp} and @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, cook for ~{1%minute} and season with @salt{}.

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes{1}, @tomato purée{30%g} and @water{400%ml} together with the @vegetable stock powder{1}. Stir to dissolve and bring the mixture to the boil.

Add the @red split lentils{100%g} and chickpeas to the soup. Simmer until the lentils are soft, ~{20-25%minutes}. 

> If the lentils need a little longer to cook, that's fine!

5 mins before the lentils are cooked, stir the @king prawns{150%g} into the lentils and continue to simmer until the prawns are cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once the lentils are cooked, season to taste with salt and @pepper{}. Meanwhile, pop your @plain naans{2} on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with salt and pepper. Toast under your #grill{} until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Serve the spiced Moroccan soup in #bowls{} with the coriander sprinkled over and a spoon of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and serve with the naans on the side. Enjoy!

> MOD Step 4: If you've decided to add prawns to your meal, 5 mins before the lentils are cooked, stir the prawns into the lentils and continue to simmer until the prawns are cooked through, 4-5 mins. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle. Continue with the rest of the recipe as instructed.